<paragraph blockId="4.[175,1005,991,1570]" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,257,991,1012]" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Male.</emphasis>
Aedeagus about 
<quantity box="[427,512,991,1012]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="0.65">0.65 mm</quantity>
in length (
<figureCitation box="[614,764,991,1012]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[169,208,888,907]" captionTargetBox="[149,977,194,865]" captionTargetId="figure-230@7.[148,978,194,866]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 26–31. Armostus spp. 26, 28, and 30, aedeagus, ventral view. 27, 29, and 31, lateral view. 26 and 27, Armostus schenklingi (d’Orchymont); 28 and 29, A. nigricans, new species; 30 and 31, A. crenulatus (Régimbart). Scale: 0.2 mm for Figs. 26–31." pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Figs. 28 and 29</figureCitation>
); median lobe about 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="0.54">0.54 mm</quantity>
in length, slender in general, apically and simply pointed in ventral view, almost straight and narrowing from basal 1/5 towards apex in lateral view; parameres about 
<quantity box="[175,265,1071,1092]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="0.43">0.43 mm</quantity>
in length; lateral sclerites of genital segment almost symmetric, apically pointed, and about 1.8 times as long as a middle sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[740,813,1098,1119]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[197,236,953,972]" captionTargetBox="[296,883,195,930]" captionTargetId="figure-222@6.[295,885,194,931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14–25. Armostus spp. 14–17, prosternum, lateral view; 18–20 and 22, mesoventrite and metaventrite; 21, right lateral area of metaventrite; 23–25, genital segment. 14, 18, and 23, Armostus schenklingi (d’Orchymont); 15, 19, and 24, A. nigricans, new species; 16, 20, 21, and 25, A. crenulatus (Régimbart); 17 and 22, A. ohyamatensis, new species. Scale A: 0.1 mm for Figs. 14–17; B: 0.5 mm for Figs. 18–22; C: 0.2 mm for Figs. 23–25." pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
