<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[175,1005,991,1570]" lastBlockId="5.[148,977,907,1087]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1336,1357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[310,499,1337,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricans" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[310,499,1337,1358]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Armostus nigricans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[514,634,1337,1358]" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(d'Orchymont, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="d'Orchymont" baseAuthorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shenklingi">
<emphasis box="[773,900,1337,1358]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">A. shenklingi</emphasis>
(d’Orchymont, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by having pronotal punctations composed of small and large punctures (
<figureCitation box="[582,643,1390,1411]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[197,236,874,893]" captionTargetBox="[288,891,195,851]" captionTargetId="figure-290@4.[287,892,194,852]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 2–7. Armostus spp. 2–7), body. 6) and 7), dorsal color. 2), 6), and 7), Armostus schenklingi (d’Orchymont); 3), A. nigricans, new species; 4), A. crenulatus (Régimbart); 5), A. ohyamatensis, new species. Scale: 1 mm for Figs. 2–7." pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), elytra widest approximately 1/7 at base, and a narrow yellowish brown patch on it (
<figureCitation box="[641,699,1416,1437]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[169,208,831,850]" captionTargetBox="[283,840,196,808]" captionTargetId="figure-238@5.[282,843,194,810]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 8–13. Armostus spp. dorsal color. 8), Armostus nigricans, new species; 9–12), A. crenulatus (Régimbart); 13), A. ohyamatensis, new species. Scale: 1 mm for Figs. 8–13." pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). In contrast, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="d' Orchymont" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[831,966,1417,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schenklingi">
<emphasis box="[831,966,1417,1438]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">A. schenklingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has pronotal punctures, all of the same size, elytra are widest approximately 1/3 at base (
<figureCitation box="[182,242,1470,1491]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[197,236,874,893]" captionTargetBox="[288,891,195,851]" captionTargetId="figure-290@4.[287,892,194,852]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 2–7. Armostus spp. 2–7), body. 6) and 7), dorsal color. 2), 6), and 7), Armostus schenklingi (d’Orchymont); 3), A. nigricans, new species; 4), A. crenulatus (Régimbart); 5), A. ohyamatensis, new species. Scale: 1 mm for Figs. 2–7." pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), and the yellowish brown patch on elytra is wide (
<figureCitation box="[739,868,1470,1491]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[197,236,874,893]" captionTargetBox="[288,891,195,851]" captionTargetId="figure-290@4.[287,892,194,852]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 2–7. Armostus spp. 2–7), body. 6) and 7), dorsal color. 2), 6), and 7), Armostus schenklingi (d’Orchymont); 3), A. nigricans, new species; 4), A. crenulatus (Régimbart); 5), A. ohyamatensis, new species. Scale: 1 mm for Figs. 2–7." pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Figs. 6 and 7</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[887,1005,1470,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricans" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[887,1005,1470,1491]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">A. nigricans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[175,289,1496,1517]" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
is also related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sharp, 1890" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1890" box="[456,675,1496,1517]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="optatus">
<emphasis box="[456,552,1496,1517]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">A. optatus</emphasis>
Sharp, 1890
</taxonomicName>
, but is separated from it by having the elytra widest about 1/7 at base and sharply narrowed towards apex from the maximal points (
<figureCitation box="[334,389,1549,1570]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[169,200,717,736]" captionTargetBox="[343,781,195,695]" captionTargetId="figure-374@3.[342,782,194,696]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Habitus, Armostus nigricans, new species. Scale: 1 mm." pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1890" box="[516,612,1549,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="optatus">
<emphasis box="[516,612,1549,1570]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">A. optatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the elytra is widest about 1/3 at base and gradually narrowed. Moreover, the present new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Hebauer 2002" authorityName="Hebauer" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuneatus">
<emphasis box="[779,890,907,928]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">A. cuneatus</emphasis>
Hebauer 2002
</taxonomicName>
, in appearance, but can be distinguished from the latter by having the concolorous dorsum except for the apex of elytra (
<figureCitation box="[525,586,960,981]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[169,208,831,850]" captionTargetBox="[283,840,196,808]" captionTargetId="figure-238@5.[282,843,194,810]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 8–13. Armostus spp. dorsal color. 8), Armostus nigricans, new species; 9–12), A. crenulatus (Régimbart); 13), A. ohyamatensis, new species. Scale: 1 mm for Figs. 8–13." pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hebauer" authorityYear="2002" box="[721,835,960,981]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuneatus">
<emphasis box="[721,835,960,981]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">A. cuneatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the head and pronotum are black and the elytra are shining reddish brown with the testaceous apex and sides.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption pageId="5" pageNumber="100" startId="5.[169,208,831,850]" targetBox="[283,840,196,808]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[148,978,831,874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[169,271,831,850]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Figs. 8–13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[292,418,831,851]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[292,371,832,851]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Armostus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
dorsal color. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[549,573,831,850]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">8),</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[583,754,832,851]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricans" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[583,754,832,851]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Armostus nigricans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[770,879,831,850]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[893,947,831,850]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">9–12),</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Regimbart)" baseAuthorityName="Regimbart" baseAuthorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">A. crenulatus</emphasis>
(Régimbart)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[359,393,855,874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">13),</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[399,539,855,874]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Armostus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ohyamatensis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[399,539,855,874]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">A. ohyamatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[551,657,855,874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. Scale: 1 mm for Figs. 8–13.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="100" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[148,977,907,1087]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[172,288,1039,1060]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Etymology.</emphasis>
